HEADWORD: Tachylyte
<hw>Tach"y*lyte</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>tachy`s</grk> quick + <grk>ly`ein</grk> to dissolve.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A vitreous form of basalt; -- so called because
decomposable by acids and readily fusible.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

